<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The limit function of Zend_Db_Select works the other way round than the Mysqls Limit statement (for example $select-&gt;limit(30, 0) translates to LIMIT 0,30). For convenience users it should be considered to throw an Exception on usage of $select-&gt;limit(0, 30) to show miss-usage.</p>

<p>Currently using limit(0,30) leads to the limit statement to be left out completly in assembling which can easily be overseen.</p>

